mage advertisements became a privileged cultural form to make people experience the qualities and uses of branded commodities, to articulate visions of a 'good life', and to incite social relationships. Abandoning a conventional delineation of fields by medium, country, or period, this book suggests a lateral view. It charts the audiovisual history of advertising by focussing on objects (products and services), screens (exhibition, programming, physical media), practices (production, marketing), and intermediaries (ad agencies). In this way, the book develops new historical, methodological, and theoretical perspectives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aTheater commercials (Motion pictures)xHistory. 4aFilm Studies. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aMedia Studies. 4aSociology and Social History. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Advertising & Promotion.2bisacsh  ascreen advertising, sponsored film, non-theatrical film, cinema studies, media industry studies.1 aFlorin, Bo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVonderau, Patrick, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVonderau, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZimmermann, Yvonne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aZimmermann, Yvonne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business